>
  <div class="page prose">
    <span class="pill">About</span>
    <h1 style="margin-top:12px;">About Janaushdhi</h1>
    <p>
      Janaushdhi is a free, ad-free price-intelligence tool for the
      <strong>Pradhan Mantri Bhartiya Janaushadhi Pariyojana (PMBJP)</strong> — the Government of India's
      flagship scheme to make quality generic medicines affordable for all.
    </p>
    <p>
      We scrape the official product list at <a href="https://www.janaushadhi.gov.in/" rel="noopener external">janaushadhi.gov.in</a>
      daily and publish the catalogue in a clean, fast, searchable interface. Part of the
      <a href="https://oriz.in/">Oriz</a> family of small static sites.
    </p>

    <h2>No ads. No tracking.</h2>
    <p>
      This is a public-health surface. We do not run AdSense, EthicalAds, or any ad slot. No analytics that fingerprint visitors.
      Hosting is free-tier static (Cloudflare Pages). We may surface a single sponsor block in the footer in future for sustainability.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      Prices on this site are scraped from janaushadhi.gov.in and may lag the official source by up to 24 hours.
      Brand MRP comparisons are illustrative and may vary by retailer, batch, and date.
      <strong>Always consult a registered pharmacist or doctor before substituting any medication.</strong>
      This site is independent and not affiliated with the Government of India, BPPI, or PMBJP.
    </p>

    <h2>Open source</h2>
    <p>
      MIT-licensed source available at
      <a href="https://github.com/chirag127/oriz-janaushdhi-app" rel="noopener external">github.com/chirag127/oriz-janaushdhi-app</a>.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top:32px;"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/browse/">Browse the catalogue →</a></p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
